msContents.summary: Commentary on the Zīj Gūrgānī, also known as the Zīj-i jadīd-i Sultānī, which comprised tables of calendar calculations, trigonometry, planets, and stars compiled from observations made at the observatory in Samarqand, completed in 1447. The tables themselves are not included.

msItem.title: Sharḥ-i Zīj Gūrgānī
msItem.author: Qūshjī, ʻAlī ibn Muḥammad, d. 1474 or 5

supportDesc.extent: 409 leaves : 177 x 128 (111 x 72) mm. bound to 177 x 138 mm

collation.p: Paper, 409 + i; 41 gatherings, alternating between 8 and 12 leaves, with 1 extra leaf added to the last gathering; [1-409], modern foliation in pencil, upper left recto. Catchwords on each leaf, lower left verso.

decoDesc.decoNote: Numerous diagrams in red ink; selected words and phrases in red.

binding.p: Contemporary morocco with flap, blind-stamped medallions on covers and flap.

origin.p: Written in Persia, now Iran, in A.H. 899 (1493-1494, colophon, f. 409r).

history.provenance: Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Dec. 2000.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2011.
